# Railway Environment Variables – Basecamp Backend
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy these into Railway → Project → Variables
# Values shown are examples; replace with your real secrets.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Set automatically by Railway (do NOT set manually) ───────────
# PORT                          set by Railway at runtime
# DATABASE_URL                  set by Railway PostgreSQL plugin

# ── ASP.NET Core ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Production

# ── Database (only needed if you are NOT using the Railway plugin) ─
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@host:5432/dbname

# ── Identity / Security ──────────────────────────────────────────
# If you add Data Protection or cookie keys later, put them here.
# DataProtection__KeyLifetime=90

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO SET IN RAILWAY:
#   1. Open your Railway project
#   2. Click the service → Variables tab
#   3. Add each key/value pair
#   4. Railway automatically redeploys
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
